At <a3_0>14,000,000 square kilometres<a3_0/> (5,400,000 square miles), it is the fifth-largest continent in area after <b8_0><b11_0>Asia, Africa, North America, and South America<b8_0/>.<b11_0/> For comparison, <b12_0>Antarctica<b12_0/> is nearly twice the size of Australia.
